f=AI & Agents/proto/custom/rapid-prototyping-method/SKILL.md · in=Fidelity discipline inside cage: build LOWEST-fidelity prototype answer manifest's hypothesis, timebox hard, decide rather polish. catalog's three-line marketplace entry, built out custom agent prototypes specifically. · p=Prototypes fail two ways: crude answer question, polished they become product prematurely (and nobody wants archive them sunk cost sabotages verdict). Right-sized fidelity protects answer verdict. · wu=Choosing what actually build after manifest criteria exist., Mid-prototype scope creep ("while we're it, let's also...")., Timebox check-ins. · st:/ Protocol=FIDELITY LADDER (pick lowest rung answer hypothesis): **Paper** skill drafts trace walkthroughs (no execution). Answers: "is routing/method coherent?" **Wizard-of-Oz** human/existing agent plays missing part. Answers: "is output valuable?" **Single-skill** one real skill cage, rest stubbed. Answers: "does core mechanism work?" **Full-shape** near-complete agent cage. Answers: integration questions; requires justification rungs 1–3 couldn't answer. TIMEBOX (per rung: `<FILL_IN: suggested 1–2 days paper, 3–5 single-skill reasoning-based>`, always inside manifest expiry) BUILD (that rung only) CHECK (can answer hypothesis yet? yes stop building, start measuring) DECIDE (feed verdict; don't polish). · in=Justify rung manifest: "why can't one rung lower answer this?" default answer fidelity questions DOWN. Scope creep test: addition change what frozen criteria measure? it's polish refused. Stubs labeled loudly stubbed capability looks real contaminates eval). Timebox breach automatic fidelity review: usually hypothesis big (split one hypothesis prototype, kit rule). Nothing built skips frontmatter/provenance, even paper drafts (kit rule 3). · of=Fidelity justification (manifest line), rung-labeled build artifacts, timebox log. · pr=Lowest fidelity answers question; default direction down., Timebox rung, prototype., Decide, don't polis